div.p:
Considering that world peace can be
safeguarded only by creative efforts commensurate with the dangers
which menace it;

Convinced that the contribution which an
organized and vital Europe can make to civilization is indispensable
to the maintenance of peaceful relations;

Aware that Europe can build itself only by
concrete achievements creating first a true solidarity and by the
establishment of common basis for economic development;

Desirous of cooperating by expansion of their
basic production in raising the standard of living and by the
advancement of peaceful accomplishments;
